{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Candied Mint","content":["Place sugar in mixing bowl and grind <nobr>10 sec\/speed 9<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside. Lay a piece of baking paper out on a flat surface.","Place egg white in mixing bowl and mix <nobr>5 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl. Using tongs, coat each mint leaf lightly in egg white then in reserved sugar. Arrange leaves on baking paper and set aside to dry in a cool, dry place for approx. 24 hours. Reserve remaining sugar and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Cake","content":["The next day, preheat oven to 180°C. Line a spring form cake tin (Ø 24 cm) with baking paper.","Place courgettes in mixing bowl and chop <nobr>2 sec\/speed 5<\/nobr>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place hemp milk, sugar, oil and eggs in mixing bowl then mix <nobr>30 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>.","Add reserved courgettes and mix <nobr>10 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt then mix <nobr>15 sec\/speed 3<\/nobr>. Transfer to prepared tin. Bake for 35-40 minutes (180°C) until a skewer inserted in centre comes out clean. Remove from tin and allow to cool on a wire rack.","Once cool, garnish with reserved crystallised mint leaves and dust with remaining reserved sugar. Serve in slices."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Candied Mint","content":["50 g caster sugar","1 egg white, from large egg","12 fresh mint leaves, for garnish"]},{"title":"Cake","content":["350 g courgettes, cut in pieces (approx. 2 courgettes)","120 g hemp milk","200 g caster sugar","100 g oil (e.g. sunflower or groundnut)","2 large eggs","165 g plain flour","45 g cocoa powder","1 tsp baking powder","1 pinch fine sea salt"]}],"id":"r154761","imageLink":"https:\/\/2.bp.blogspot.com\/-pNb8YPHrfys\/XZWqcPVl9rI\/AAAAAAAAfX4\/vUrHOZwd4Okks1VgZHV9AcuJ9GGapXW7ACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_LTEz9w9icDrIo3zD.png","title":"Courgette and Cocoa Cake","publishedAt":"2018-02-05T